00:46:39.570 --> 00:46:43.620
And I'm asking-- I'm coaching
my 10-year-old's baseball team

00:46:43.620 --> 00:46:46.520
and I'd like to hear
your thoughts on this.

00:46:46.520 --> 00:46:48.500
STEVEN KOTLER: That's
a great question.

00:46:48.500 --> 00:46:53.110
So as you were talking, I don't
know if there are upper limits.

00:46:53.110 --> 00:46:54.070
I really don't.

00:46:54.070 --> 00:46:55.830
Age-related limits, I
realized as you were talking,

00:46:55.830 --> 00:46:57.550
I was like, God, I've never
even asked that question

00:46:57.550 --> 00:46:58.760
or even thought about that.

00:46:58.760 --> 00:47:01.750
So there may be upper limit
stuff that I don't know about.

00:47:01.750 --> 00:47:04.600
Kids are actually very flow
prone because developmentally

00:47:04.600 --> 00:47:06.370
their prefrontal
cortex doesn't finish

00:47:06.370 --> 00:47:09.122
developing until you're 25.

00:47:09.122 --> 00:47:11.080
That's why your nose is
the last thing to grow.

00:47:11.080 --> 00:47:14.560
It's space for your
prefrontal cortex.

00:47:14.560 --> 00:47:16.120
So they're
developmentally geared

00:47:16.120 --> 00:47:17.680
towards transient
hypofrontality,

00:47:17.680 --> 00:47:19.360
and their brainwaves
are actually

00:47:19.360 --> 00:47:22.040
naturally closer to alpha.

00:47:22.040 --> 00:47:23.110
Adults are in beta.

00:47:23.110 --> 00:47:26.140
Kids tend to be closer to alpha.

00:47:26.140 --> 00:47:27.600
So kids are flow prone.

00:47:27.600 --> 00:47:31.090
In my book Rise of Superman, we
talked about the crazy places

00:47:31.090 --> 00:47:32.350
it's showing up.

00:47:32.350 --> 00:47:35.110
Flow coaching has gotten
