00:47:44.470 --> 00:47:49.180
And one of the reasons is
because flow coaching has been

00:47:49.180 --> 00:47:51.730
in action sports for longer.

00:47:51.730 --> 00:47:53.920
In mainstream
sports, it popped in.

00:47:53.920 --> 00:47:57.400
Jimmy Johnson said the Dallas
Cowboys won the Super Bowl back

00:47:57.400 --> 00:47:59.860
in the '90s and he
credited Csikszentmihalyi.

00:47:59.860 --> 00:48:04.210
So flow has been in sports for
a while, but not at the level--

00:48:04.210 --> 00:48:05.950
those traditional
bat and ball sports

00:48:05.950 --> 00:48:08.470
are little more conservative.

00:48:08.470 --> 00:48:12.040
And action sports, they weren't
even sports back in the '90s,

00:48:12.040 --> 00:48:13.450
right?

00:48:13.450 --> 00:48:15.760
So there's been a lot
more flow coaching.

00:48:15.760 --> 00:48:17.200
We're seeing
interesting results.

00:48:17.200 --> 00:48:18.940
A friend of ours--
we are working

00:48:18.940 --> 00:48:23.380
with a guy in Minnesota who
is doing a bunch of flow

00:48:23.380 --> 00:48:24.550
work in grade school.

00:48:24.550 --> 00:48:26.680
And they're using
the flow profile

00:48:26.680 --> 00:48:30.100
with kids, trying to figure
out what's their dominant flow

00:48:30.100 --> 00:48:32.980
area, and then having them do
a lot of independent studies

00:48:32.980 --> 00:48:33.620
over the years.

00:48:33.620 --> 00:48:35.440
And their idea is that
if they can get them

00:48:35.440 --> 00:48:37.930
into high school already
knowing what produces the most

00:48:37.930 --> 00:48:40.346
flow in their life and what
they're most passionate about,

00:48:40.346 --> 00:48:42.010
they'll have a leg up.

00:48:42.010 --> 00:48:43.497
So we're doing
some of that work.

00:48:43.497 --> 00:48:44.330
We're looking at it.

00:48:44.330 --> 00:48:45.310
But there's a ways to go.

00:48:45.310 --> 00:48:46.143
AUDIENCE: Thank you.

